pwm: sky1: fix Kconfig entry indentation

The CIX PWM patch adds " config PWM_SKY1" with a leading space, which is not
valid Kconfig style and can be parsed incorrectly depending on context. Make it
a normal top-level config entry.

---
diff --git a/drivers/pwm/Kconfig b/drivers/pwm/Kconfig
--- a/drivers/pwm/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/pwm/Kconfig
@@ -842,7 +842,7 @@ config PWM_XILINX
 	  To compile this driver as a module, choose M here: the module
 	  will be called pwm-xilinx.
 
- config PWM_SKY1
+config PWM_SKY1
 	tristate "CIX Sky1 PWM support"
 	depends on ARCH_CIX || COMPILE_TEST
 	help
